cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is primarily focused on image tampering detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning networks and statistical analysis also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with image compression and manipulation, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of probability maps and classification results to locate tampered areas suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
